    <div style="background: #c8e6c9; border-left: 4px solid #4caf50; padding: 15px; margin: 20px 0; border-radius: 4px;">
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">⚡ Parallelization Opportunities</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Parallel Work (Week 1)</strong>: #1C.1 (endpoint) and #1C.2 (scope system) can be developed in parallel as they target different layers</li>
            <li><strong>Parallel Work (Week 2)</strong>: #1C.3 (CLI script), #1C.4 (docs), and #1C.5 (testing) can proceed in parallel - testing drives docs refinement</li>
            <li><strong>Sequential Critical Path</strong>: Phase 1B → #1C.1 → #1C.2 → #1C.3 (must complete in this order for functionality)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <hr style="margin: 30px 0;" />

    <h2>✅ Validation & Success Criteria</h2>

    <div style="background: #e8f5e9; border: 1px solid #4caf50; border-radius: 4px; padding: 15px; margin: 20px 0;">
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">Phase 1C Success Checklist</h3>
        <ul style="line-height: 1.8;">
            <li>✅ <strong>Endpoint Working</strong>: POST /api/token/cli-setup generates valid tokens, returns JSON response with token + .env format</li>
            <li>✅ <strong>CLI Script Functional</strong>: <code>comserv-cli token generate</code> calls endpoint successfully, <code>comserv-cli token list</code> shows all tokens</li>
            <li>✅ <strong>Token Use in API Calls</strong>: Bearer token authentication works: <code>curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $KEY" https://comserv/api/todo/create</code></li>
            <li>✅ <strong>Scope Enforcement</strong>: Out-of-scope requests return 403; in-scope requests succeed</li>
            <li>✅ <strong>Expiration Working</strong>: Expired tokens rejected with 401; can be extended via CLI</li>
            <li>✅ <strong>Revocation Working</strong>: Revoked tokens rejected; appear as revoked in <code>comserv-cli token list</code></li>
            <li>✅ <strong>Documentation Complete</strong>: All endpoints documented with examples (bash, perl, python, curl)</li>
            <li>✅ <strong>Grok Integration Tested</strong>: Grok can authenticate and create todos via API token</li>
            <li>✅ <strong>Audit Trail Logging</strong>: All token operations logged; admin dashboard shows usage history</li>
            <li>✅ <strong>Security Hardened</strong>: Tokens never stored plaintext, config files have 600 permissions, rate limiting active</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

